Jessie,<br><br>
The Vietnam War generated its own mythology and &quot;language&quot;, so to speak, much of which was spontaneous and impossible to trace.<br><br>
The phrase:<br><br>
&quot;Don't mean nuthin.&quot;<br><br>
was commonly used to express the meaninglessness of the war and what happened in combat. It was used in any situation where emotionless and meaningless things were experienced. Many who fought in Vietnam were emptionally numbed. It was a phrase to get around the pain of it all.<br><br>
I am not a linguist, just a Vietnam Veteran who remembers.<br><br>

